Memgraph is a streaming graph application platform that helps you wrangle your streaming data, build sophisticated models that you can query in real-time.[1] We have dozens of datasets that we have are showcasing on our site or in our app [2], [3], and [4].

We would like to build our models, datasets, and apps around real life examples and data.

Do you know and good sources like the one from Jure Leskovac [5]?

[1] https://memgraph.com/

[2] https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=31395478

[3] https://memgraph.com/blog/gas-pipelines-in-europe

[4] https://playground.memgraph.com/

[5] https://snap.stanford.edu/data/

stories.text:
I am researching software engineering internships to share with my students, who are from a variety of backgrounds (high school, college, currently working, and some unemployed folks). They've all have less than 1 year of experience coding and are looking for opportunities to get some more hands on experience.

What are some good places to look for opportunities that would be valuable to them?
